{"type":"message","id":"76cdf172","parentId":"53c6fb4d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:41:23.367Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants me to add backup models/providers to the OpenClaw config. He wants to keep minimax as the main one. I need to find the config file and add the API keys for wandb, huggingface, and github - though github isn't really a model provider. Let me check the OpenClaw config.\n\nActually, thinking about this more - the API keys he gave me earlier are:\n- WANDB_API_KEY - Weights & Biases\n- HF_TOKEN - HuggingFace\n- GITHUB_PAT - GitHub\n\nThese aren't really LLM providers. For backup models, Zach probably wants things like OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, etc. \n\nBut looking back at what he said about adding backup models and providers using those API keys - he's being sarcastic about the GitHub PAT not being a model provider, but he's actually asking me to configure backup providers with the keys he just set up, starting with wandb and huggingface.","thinkingSignature":"a728c66eb1953f08da8001c933a0b50ee1fb79a925e0589a3ed9063c7a46d959"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_e6jwc2wb6dfb_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"~/.openclaw/config.toml"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":226,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":12237,"totalTokens":16752,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774345274247}}
