{"type":"message","id":"cb629401","parentId":"8b3eb025","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:42:29.767Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me add the backup providers properly. I'll add them after the \"modal-spark\" provider block. The providers I want to add:\n1. Groq (free tier, fast)\n2. OpenRouter (aggregator, has free models)\n3. Cohere (has free tier)\n4. HuggingFace (has free Inference API)\n\nFor HuggingFace, I should use the HF_TOKEN. But actually, HuggingFace's Inference API doesn't typically use a token in the same way - it's usually for their paid Inference Endpoints. For the free Inference API, you just use `anonymous` or no auth. The HF_TOKEN is more for huggingface_hub Python library auth.\n\n\nI'll stick with adding providers that have clear free tier support: Groq with the `llama-3.1-8b-instant` model, OpenRouter which aggregates various free options, Cohere with their command models, and Google AI Studio for their free gemini models. Let me format this properly for the config file.","thinkingSignature":"fa2017f838e854d35c989401bb609a0c29f9ef850a2bf4391866da97aba919aa"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6q0ja3ssk8tg_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\openclaw.json","old_string":"      \"modal-spark\": {\n        \"baseUrl\": \"https://toxzak-svg--spark-ollama-qwen-generate.modal.run\",\n        \"apiKey\": \"modal\",\n        \"api\": \"ollama\",\n        \"models\": [\n          {\n            \"id\": \"qwen2.5:7b\",\n            \"name\": \"Qwen 2.5 7B (Modal T4)\",\n            \"api\": \"ollama\",\n            \"reasoning\": false,\n            \"input\": [\n              \"text\"\n            ],\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"input\": 0,\n              \"output\": 0,\n              \"cacheRead\": 0,\n              \"cacheWrite\": 0\n            },\n            \"contextWindow\": 32768,\n            \"maxTokens\": 4096\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n 